61-years old Paul Helmend a Fourways, Gauteng resident died in a hiking accident when he fell 30 meters down a steep embankment in the Drakensberg region. He was hiking with his family when the accident happened. His son tried to revive him with CPR but was unsuccessful. The staff at the hotel also tried to assist and contacted SAPS Search and Rescue. Recovery of the body was completed by SAPS Air wing this afternoon.